SIMPLE: tossing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tossing
<hw>Toss"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of throwing
upward; a rising and falling suddenly; a rolling and tumbling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A process which
consists in washing ores by violent agitation in water, in order to
separate the lighter or earthy particles; -- called also
<altname>tozing</altname>, and <altname>treloobing</altname>, in
Cornwall.</def> <au>Pryce.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A process for refining
tin by dropping it through the air while melted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tosspot</ent>⟦br⟧
